cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.SE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.AR (Architecture), as it discusses the architectural differences between two processors and their impact on performance. It could also belong to cs.PF (Performance), as it evaluates the performance of HPC proxy applications. Additionally, it may fit into cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) due to its focus on HPC applications. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it challenges the common wisdom in HPC and suggests a potential shift in hardware design.
